							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/brendan-borrell/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Brendan Borrell is a contributing writer at <em>Hakai Magazine</em>, where he has reported on the most notorious fishing criminal in New England, the last hippie outlaws of Hawai‘i’s Kalalau Valley, and the future of Havana’s crumbling infrastructure. His writing on science and the environment has also appeared in dozens of other outlets, including <em>The Atlantic</em>, <em>Bloomberg Businessweek</em>, <em>National Geographic</em>, <em>Scientific American</em>, <em>Smithsonian</em>, and <em>Outside</em>. He currently lives in Los Angeles, California. Photo by Antonio Bussiello</p></div>
